<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 3200, 4200, 4300, 4400, 7300, 7400, 7500, 7600, 8500, 8600 Models
        Built Before 05/20/2003 - ELECTRONIC GAUGE CLUSTER AND AUXILIARY GAUGE SWITCH PACK - REMOVE AND INSTALL - EGC
        SWITCH PACK SWITCHES
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="0">
        <title>EGC SWITCH PACK SWITCHES</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk document="s082503_137.xml" xrefid="f0825487">EGC Exploded View.</hotlnk>
            <xref refid="f0825487"/>
        </para>
        <para>Switches are removed through the front of the switch pack. To remove a switch:</para>
        <seqlist>
            <item>
                <para>Remove the back cover from the switch pack.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Squeeze the switch release tabs, behind the switch pack.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Push the switch out of the switch pack body.</para>
            </item>
        </seqlist>
        <para>To install a switch reverse the removal process.</para>
    </svcproc>
